.TH "omap2430_clk_i2chs_find_idlest" 9 "omap2430_clk_i2chs_find_idlest" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
omap2430_clk_i2chs_find_idlest \- return CM_IDLEST info for 2430 I2CHS
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" omap2430_clk_i2chs_find_idlest
.BI "(struct clk_hw_omap *clk "  ","
.BI "struct clk_omap_reg *idlest_reg "  ","
.BI "u8 *idlest_bit "  ","
.BI "u8 *idlest_val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "clk" 12
struct clk * being enabled
.IP "idlest_reg" 12
void __iomem ** to store CM_IDLEST reg address into
.IP "idlest_bit" 12
pointer to a u8 to store the CM_IDLEST bit shift into
.IP "idlest_val" 12
pointer to a u8 to store the CM_IDLEST indicator
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
OMAP2430 I2CHS CM_IDLEST bits are in CM_IDLEST1_CORE, but the
CM_*CLKEN bits are in CM_{I,F}CLKEN2_CORE.  This custom function
passes back the correct CM_IDLEST register address for I2CHS
modules.  No return value.
